adni,Classification of Alzheimer’s Disease by Combination of Convolutional and Recurrent Neural Networks Using FDG-PET Images,https://doi.org/10.3389/fninf.2018.00035,openalex_adni_M_ml_top350.csv,https://openalex.org/W2805773775,2018,include_any_use,True,121460,html_plus_pdf,,Handcrafted feature pipelines; Learned representation pipelines,2,1,1,0,0,0,"powerful to help understand the anatomical and neural changes of brain related to AD. Most existing methods extract the handcrafted features from images, and then design a classifier to distinguish AD from other groups. These methods highly depends on the preprocessing of brain images, including image rigid registratio","et ( Cabral et al., 2013 ). Recently, deep learning methods can take the advantage of the data privilege to extract the latent features from measurements of ROIs with different image modalities for AD classification ( Liu et al., 2015 ; Suk et al., 2015 ). Liu et al. (2015) extracted a set of latent features from",,,
